<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Donny van de Beek was spotted enjoying his new surroundings as the Manchester United new boy went on a date night with girlfriend Estelle Bergkamp on Wednesday evening. </p>

<p>The 23-year-old joined Ole Gunner Solskjaer's side from Ajax this summer in a £40m deal from the Dutch side, becoming United's first and only signing of the window thus far. </p>

<p>While it has been an unconventional time with coronavirus restrictions, Van De Beek managed to take in the scenery of Manchester as he and girlfriend Estelle, daughter of Arsenal icon Dennis Bergkamp, went out in the city for the first time.</p>

<p>Manchester United new boy has been spotted taking in his new surroundings on Wednesday</p>

<p>The Dutch star went into the city centre with girlfriend Estelle Bergkamp for the first time</p>

<p>The pair went for dinner at the plush Australasia restaurant, with 24-year-old Estelle posting a picture of the loved-up couple on her Instagram. </p>

<p>'Our first dinner together in the city,' she wrote as the United new boy posed in a grey sweater. </p>

<p>Van de Beek commented a love heart emoji while the Arsenal legend also commented on the post.  </p>

<p>Estelle also shared an image of the midfield star to her story for he 72,000 followers. </p>

<p>The loved-up couple went for dinner at the plush Australasia restaurant in the city centre </p>

<p>Estelle, 24, shared a picture of Van de Beek looking pensive as they enjoyed their date night</p>

<p>Despite United losing their Premier League opener to Crystal Palace, Van de Beek made a positive impact from the bench, as he pulled a goal back to give his new side brief hope of a comeback.</p>

<p>Solskjaer rewarded the new boy's cameo with a starting place in the side that beat Luton Town 3-0 in the Carabao Cup on Tuesday evening.</p>

<p>Van de Beek will be hoping he will be handed his first Premier League start when United travel to Brighton and Hove Albion on Saturday afternoon. </p>

<p>Estelle is the daughter of Arsenal icon Dennis Bergkamp, who shared a love heart on the post</p>
